Redescription.
Length 
1.90–2.35 mm
(
Fig. 29–32
). Integument blackish brown except for reddish apical half of rostrum, antennae and legs; on dorsum densely covered with whitish to light brown scales arranged in doubletriple row on elytral interstriae and seta-like brown scales in single median row. Rostrum (
Fig. 153–156
) slightly curved (Rl/Rw 
4.33–4.38 in
male, 
4.63–4.69 in
female; Rl/Pl 
0.80–0.93 in
male, 0.90–1.00 in female), moderately tapered from base to apex. Antennal funicle 7-segmented. Eyes convex, distinctly prominent. Pronotum transverse (Pw/Pl 1.13–1.28), with weakly rounded sides in basal half, widest at middle. Elytra oval (El/Ew 1.20–1.33; Ew/Pw 1.27–1.42), with somewhat rounded sides from base, widest in basal half. Femora (
Fig. 259–260
) with indistinct tooth. Profemora and protibiae (
Fig. 315
) without sexual characters. Claws with robust medial teeth, as long as 3/4 of claw. Male genitalia: body of penis (
Fig. 372
) slightly constricted at middle, narrowed only until near apex, with blunted tip (
Fig. 405
), as long as half of apodeme. Female genitalia: spermatheca (
Fig. 438
) with indistinct ramus and collum, robust nodus, robust cornu narrowed until near apex; spiculum ventrale (
Fig. 464
) with arms joined from base to apex.
